<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9719981943790></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9719981943790><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9719981943790>RE: uh oh....</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9719981943790#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1249 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 19th 7:29 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.75]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just an entirely prejudiced and biased viewpoint here, but since it seems likely you are going to start over may I recommend being a troll?<br><br>They are far more fun to play when roleplaying since putting a Highlander's brogue into the written form is nigh to impossible and trolls can be impolite and abusive since it is their nature.&nbsp;&nbsp;Case in point:<br>Frequently I will be found near the EC tunnel loudly proclaiming that I am SoWing, buffing, healing, and curing for 1 gold per level, but  with a 1 plat maximum.  People, in their desperation, will often come to me paying their coin for what I have to offer, so while giving them what they paid for (I do not cheat them regardless of my evil soul) I might see an Ogre or fellow Troll standing nearby.  I will proclaim in a loud voice, "Hmmmm, brudder, lemme _____ (fill in the blank with the spell of your choice) you for free."  I will then finish what I started with the paying individual-- usually recieving a /tell asking me why the Ogre got free spells, but HE has to pay!<br>Or, I make a hotbutton with the /em  stating I am holding out my filthy opened-sored hand waiting for the money before I begin casting.  Then after giving them what they want I /em coughs and spits on the _____ (elf, human, Barbie doll, etc etc).<br>Almost always gets a rise out of them...<br><br>The speech we can use is more enjoyable since we can sound like we were dropped on our heads at birth as opposed to Barbie dolls who just sound like they are from the Ozarks when they talk like that-- aside from the fact they are based on Scottish Highlanders (Mel Gibson, anyone?  FREEDOM!!!   FREEDOMMMMMMMM!!!)<br><br>The Troll is hard to play, no doubt.  The higher levels get progressively harder, I agree.  But from a roleplaying perspective they can't be beat.  I have found that the higher you get in the game you catch yourself in a never-ending cycle of kill mob, level, kill mob, level, with fancier stuff to be sure, but basically the same thing that you have been doing from your first level.  Nothing changes except the numbers that you hit for and get hit with.  <br>Look at it from this viewpoint:  your Id can come out and no one will fault you because you are being rude and crude.  Its your nature-- you are a Troll!  Try this with your Barbarian and you'll never get reinvited into groups!<br><br>Ok, I acknowledge others play this game for other reasons, every one of them legitimate, but since the shammy is your choice go one step further and REALLY do it up right.<br><br>Good luck, young (troll, I hope) shammy!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
