	   <tr><td colspan=2>I can't speak for the very high levels, but as a semi-casual player I prefer the enchanted fine steel mace.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even though it has poor melee stats (5 damage/35 delay) it has +5 WIS, so that, combined with a Charred Guardian Shield give me a +14 WIS bonus.  Eventually I will buy a ranged weapon that gives a WIS bonus.  I balance that with a "Screamer" (screaming mace) when I am out of mana.  The screamer can easily be bought for 40pp in Greater Faydark and is an excellent melee weapon.<br>As you can see, I place a premium on wisdom since that allows me to engage enemies at arms length rather than face-to-face.  I also believe I will never see the day when I achieve the level necessary to get the new "uber weapon" since it is NO DROP item and I don't play that much.  A spear is very attainable and I might get one someday, but since I started out with a club, that is where I have gained my proficiency.<br>So my vote is 1 hand blunt since that is what you start with and are most likely to use throughout your life in Norrath (assuming you are like me, a person who has to juggle a job, family, and other priorities).  On the other hand, if you have the time or a high level friend who is willing to help you out, I understand piercing is the way to go...  your call!<br>That's what makes this game so fun!<br>Good luck, young shammy!  <br><br>PS:  You ARE a troll, aren't you, young shaman?!? <br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
