<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97180373130903></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97180373130903><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97180373130903>RE: Playing Tank</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=97180373130903#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 17th 1:28 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I tanked for a group of casters just awhile back in the over there zone at lvl 39.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>If you want to take you need to spend time meleeing not kiting.  Shaman melee skill do not keep up with those of Fighters and so as we go up in lvl we have a harder time hitting and get hit more often than pure melee types.  There are many stages to the life of a shaman.  <br><br>lvl 1-13 a shaman is little more than a weak tank with some magic tricks.  Most your damage will be done with your weapon.  <br><br>lvl 14-23 Now shaman think they are durids and use kiting alot.<br><br>lvl 24-33 With spells obtained at lvl 24 you are now able to shaman solo.  Cast your quickness spell on yourself. cast slow on the mob and dot with your new dot.  Melee while the dot works.  <br>As a note it is a good idea to cast slow and dot your last two cast while kiting, and then melee before lvl 23.  <br><br>lvl 34+ with the new dot and pet your weapon will become less and less important because the pet and dots get srtonger and stronger while your ability to hit keeps going down.  At lvl 40 my weapon was doing 15% of the damage, the pet was doing 30% while the two dots did 65%.  You become a punching bag while the dots and pet kill the mob make sure to cast quickness on your pet as well as your self.  <br><br>Also cast regen on your self while soloing after lvl 24.  <br><br>Unless you can get one of the upper end spears, 2hb are the best weapons for soloing and tanking as a shaman.  <br><br>When tanking in a group only cast the posion dots it should keep the mob on you, if the casters don't over cast.  if the mob keep jumping to the caster just keep it rooted.  <br><br>at high lvl you will need to solo often to keep your melee skill at lvl.  but the good news you can shaman solo almost anywhere and go get some of the nice items <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
