	   <tr><td colspan=2>Daft as a brush, but, yeah, shamen have one solo tactic at their disposal they share with paladins (at least, prior to level 14).&nbsp;&nbsp;If you're running low on hp's, hit your opponent with a Flash of Light and step back--your opponent will stagger about randomly, allowing you to either heal yourself, or (unique to shamen) hit the MOB with a DD or DOT, or (if 9th level or over), slap a SoW on yourself and head for the hills!<br><br>Actually, they share *another* solo tactic, too, same principle--at level 14 (22 for paladins), hit your beastie with a Root and step away.  Similar benefits.<br><br>Just remember, though, this ain't so effective on casters, but you *can* escape, so long as you're out of his line of sight.  NPC casters need a clear LOS in order to start casting a spell on you--they don't need to maintain it, though, to finish it.<br>&nbsp;<br>"Here is a purse of monies...which I'm not going to give to you."</td></tr>
