	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a quick warning with the "Shaman Dance of Death" aka Med/cannabilize.&nbsp;&nbsp;If it is a close fight (solo at least), avoid the temptation to cannabilize down really low to get that extra little mana to get another spell off unless you are completely sure the fight is in the bag.  Mobs have a tendency to frenzy on you when you least expect it.  There is nothing worse than seeing a mob turn to run, you canning to get enough mana to nuke it down (most often in an area where others assist it), and suddenly the monster deciding since you are low on hp to frenzy on you.<br>I canned down to about half a bubb at a zone line to finish off a MOB the other day when it ran (all my DoT's had worn off and I was very LOM) when suddenly it turned, double hit me for a total of 120 damage, and knocked me out.  Regen started to do its thing while it missed me, but then it got in one shot right before I went conscious again.  Heh, lesson learned the hard way =)<br>Gorthin 37 Shaman who hasn't been playing since the wife is on Vacation<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
