	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, this is incorrect.&nbsp;&nbsp;Inner fire does indeed heal, I used it for that very purpose just last night.  <br><br>Going back to somebody's post way up top about grouping with a warrior or a cleric or an enchanter or whatever, I have found that I prefer the company of a druid over just about anyone, for the following reasons;  <br>1) Buffs.  They get the skin line, which beats ass on our inner fire, hands down, and their strength buffs are good.  We get everything else.<br>2) Dots.  We get poison and disease, they get fire and magic.  4 dots, no waiting.<br>3) Snare.  Nuff said<br>4) Pets.  Now that druids get that teddy bear pet to go with Fluffy the Wondermutt, pet kiting becomes even groovier.<br>5) Shapechange.  Add another bear and wolf to the pets, and it's barnyard fun.<br>6) Teleports.  Damn unfair that we don't get it, but they do, and that's good enough.<br>7) Nukes.  Neither our nor druids nukes are mage/wizzy caliber, but you can still play Mob-Pong.  Great fun!<br>8) This Space Intentionally Left Blank<br>9) Most druids are able to wear small armors, and most shaman can wear large.  It's the Jack Sprat factor.<br>10) And finally, 2 healers are better than 1.  <br><br>Yes, druids and shamans have a lot of spells that overlap, but we only have 8 slots to mem spells in, might as well make best use of what we have available.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
