	   <tr><td colspan=2>With my level 10 shaman i found that light healing was just as effective as inner fire for downtime healing. Why? Becuase inner fire has a longer cast and recast time, and it will take a lot more casts to heal the tank. In all that time you were healing with inner fire, you would have been done with light healing MUCH quicker, and have had time to med. If you still want to use inner fie thats fine, but i would still recommend using light healer for acctual fights when you might need to heal quick not effiently. Just my 20000cp that are weighing me down =:-) .<br><br>Corpusnuntia/Divineshadow/Naltec/Natalos/Plantmaster/Sunsong/Zuranthium<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
